`template/` is a project scaffold: it ships the git-level config (`.gitattributes`) that governs how generated `.ctx`/`rollup.ctx` files under `.context/` merge, plus a `scripts/` subtree that becomes the CI/lint gate and CTX-tooling sync mechanism in any project scaffolded from this template.

The only cross-cutting coupling at this level is indirect: `.gitattributes` declares the `ctx-regenerate` merge driver for `.context/**/*.ctx` and `rollup.ctx`, but that driver isn't implemented anywhere in this tree yet (no `merge.ctx-regenerate.driver` entry exists) — conflicts must currently be resolved by hand via `ctx-resummarize`. Anyone changing the `.context/` tree layout or `.ctx` naming convention (which lives in the tooling scripts, not here) must keep the `.gitattributes` patterns in sync or the merge driver silently stops matching.

`scripts/` is the only real content subtree and is self-contained; its check-script output contract and sync-pipeline marker conventions are documented there and don't otherwise touch `.gitattributes`.

intent_divergence: no intent.md exists for this directory, so no claim can be checked.